The paper deals with distributed estimation of a random field observed by sensors, which involves information flow and gathering. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of linear distributed estimators, which may fall under the Machine Learning (cs.MA) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also considers the behavior of the estimator under noise, which may relate to the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
